@wololo-ayoyoyo Personalities are mostly built up from memories as you learn knowledge and acquire habits from the moment you are born. DNA specific to the brain's foundation and function would be the remaining amount as no human will act the same even if they live the exact same life. 

Nothing can pinpoint and cleanly erase memories to a 100% without messing with personality.
Also seems like terrible customer support to not have a way to restore such a thing or at least assess the reasoning behind the product's actions. Rip human rights and customer service.
